Huawei’s new Mate 20 Lite is set to launch in South Africa on 5 October 2018, and local retailers have begun to list the device online. Technomobi has listed the blue and black Huawei Mate 20 smartphones on its website, with the device priced at R9,499. Huawei’s Mate 20 Lite sports dual front and dual rear cameras encased in a modern smartphone chassis. The device runs Android 8.1 and features a FullView display with an 81% screen-to-body ratio. Artificial intelligence features power a number of unique functions on the device, including the ability to improve pictures taken with its dual-camera systems. The Huawei Mate 20 Lite will start shipping from 5 October and customers can pre-order the device from today.